SIMPLE: nill
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nill
<hw>Nill</hw> <pr>(n⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Nilled</conjf> <pr>(n⟦icr⟧ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Nilling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>nilan</ets>,
<ets>nyllan</ets>; <ets>ne</ets> not + <ets>willan</ets> to will. See
<er>No</er>, and <er>Will</er>.]</ety> <def>Not to will; to refuse; to
reject.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Certes, said he, I <qex>nill</qex> thine offered grace.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nill</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nill
<hw>Nill</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be unwilling; to refuse to
act.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The actions of the will are ⟦ldquo⟧velle⟦rdquo⟧ and
⟦ldquo⟧nolle,⟦rdquo⟧ to will and <qex>nill</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Burton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Will he, nill he</b></col>, <cd>whether he wills it or
not; usually contracted to <altname>willy-nilly</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nill</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Nill
<hw>Nill</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Ir. & Gael. <ets>neul</ets> star,
light. Cf. <er>Nebula</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Shining sparks
thrown off from melted brass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Scales of hot iron from the forge.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nilometer</ent>⟦br⟧
